The paper deals with a problem in submodular optimization, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of stochastic variables and the focus on approximation algorithms suggest that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the lower bound result involves game theory concepts, which could place the paper in the category of computational game theory (cs.GT).
